text: A surprise visit from the Champ my first year in office. It was the greatest day. https://t.co/WjDvpmXOFx

Muhammad Ali is an ever present reminder than the most famous person in the world can be a real life hero.

He really was the greatest.
At a time when fame so often comes with questionable character...
I am just one of the many in Louisville whose heart aches for the loss of my friend, and yet, our community is better for his impact.
Muhammad Ali was a selfless giant who put principles over everything, and never forgot the city he called home.
A loud-mouthed speedster by the name of Cassius Marcellus Clay, whose fights in and out of the ring would one day make him Muhammad Ali.
I remember waiting for him at Standiford Field when he returned after beating Liston, thinking I had never seen a more perfect human being.
I remember watching every one of his championship fights.
In the ring, there was no one better. But his contributions to humanity managed to eclipse his boxing prowess.
He was a man who gained fame in a violent game, but immortality as a gentle and caring soul.
The word "champion" has never fit a man better. Muhammad Ali was a champion. A champion for peace. For justice. For equality.
My statement on the passing of #TheGreatest and Louisville's own, Muhammad Ali: https://t.co/gPWRF8L5Nk

text: Thanks to the #ACA & @kynectky, the Medicare Rx drug “donut hole” is being phased out for 89,000+ KY seniors, saving $1,108 per beneficiary.
Thanks to the #ACA & @kynectky, out-of-pocket costs for preventive health care services have been eliminated for 1.8 million Kentuckians.
Thanks to #ACA & @kynectky, 630K+ on Medicare in KY paid no out-of-pocket costs for cancer screenings, annual physicals, & preventive care.
Thanks to the #ACA & @kynectky, 137,000 consumers in KY received more than $8.9M in rebates from their health insurers in 2015 alone.
Thanks to the #ACA & @kynectky’s Medicaid expansion, more than 572,000 Kentuckians have gained Medicaid or CHIP coverage.
Thanks to the #ACA & @kynectky, 1.8 million Kentucky residents with preexisting conditions can no longer be denied the care they need.
Thanks to the #ACA & @kynectky, Kentucky’s uninsured rate has been cut by more than 63 percent.

text: Above all, these misguided GOP budgets rely on the very same thing: faith-based accounting. They'll just close their eyes and pray it works.
GOP budgets continue the myth that trickle-down economics works, but only make it easier to retain wealth & virtually impossible to gain it.
Even the nonpartisan @USCBO estimates that repeal of the ACA would increase deficit by $109 billion and cost us $1 trillion in lost revenue.
Chief among the gimmickry is the assertion that there is ANYTHING responsible about stripping healthcare from tens of millions of Americans.
When asked about the GOP budget proposals, even @TaxpayersEllis said "This isn't budgeting, it's gimmickry."
.@BudgetHawks also says Senate GOP budget savings “lack specificity, which will make it difficult to turn proposed cuts into real deficit.”
According to @BudgetHawks, the House GOP budget uses "gimmicks that circumvent budget discipline” and is “unrealistic and unspecified.”
This criticism isn’t coming just from people on the left. Conservative groups are also calling out their use of budget trickery & spin.
The GOP‘s House & Senate budgets use some remarkably acrobatic arithmetic to give the appearance of one that balances. It's mostly gimmicks.
Although GOP conferees have decided to negotiate the budget behind closed doors, the harmful realities of their proposals remain clear.
